Please upgrade to 0.3.8!

Bitcointalk

2010-08-03 23:40:18 UTC - [11]Original Post

   Version 0.3.8 adds an important security improvement.  Everyone should
   upgrade to get this change.
   The new safety feature displays a warning message in the status bar and
   locks down RPC if it detects a problem that may require an upgrade.
   If it sees a longer chain, but it canʼt process it, then it knows
   something is wrong.  It displays "WARNING: Displayed transactions may
   not be correct!  You may need to upgrade." and makes most RPC commands
   return an error.  It still keeps generating as normal, which is
   necessary for the stability of the network.
   There were important security updates in the versions before this too,
   so if you havenʼt upgraded recently, itʼs extremely important that you
   upgrade now!
   Also, donʼt forget, we recently added 2.4x faster generating thanks to
   tcatmʼs mid-state caching optimisation and BlackEyeʼs help getting ASM
   SHA-256 working.
   Download:
   [12]http://sourceforge.net/projects/bitcoin/files/Bitcoin/bitcoin-0.3.8
